modules.description: This module implements PPX derivers for generating expression and type definitions, functors, and test harnesses based on module type declarations. It works directly with OCaml's abstract syntax trees (ASTs) using `Ppxlib` types such as `structure_item`, `module_type_declaration`, and expansion contexts. It is used to automatically derive modules like `Mica` that include interpreters, test scaffolding, and core data type definitions from declarative specifications.
